print(q.dequeue())  # 3
print(q.peek())  # 2
print(q.is_empty())  # False
```

This implementation uses two stacks to simulate a queue. The `enqueue` operation adds elements to the top of the `newest_on_top` stack. The `dequeue` operation removes elements from the top of the `oldest_on_top` stack. If `oldest_on_top` is empty, it moves all elements from `newest_on_top` to `oldest_on_top` to maintain the correct order. The `peek` and `is_empty` operations work accordingly. The `size` method returns the total number of elements in both stacks.
